  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://slack.rook.io/).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nThe toolbox doesn't have a need to run privileged. The toolbox should really only be used to execute `ceph` commands, rather than need to run privileged and access the host. \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nThe changes suggested would include:\r\n- The [toolbox](https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/cluster/examples/kubernetes/ceph/toolbox.yaml) manifest can remove:\r\n   -  `privileged: true`\r\n   - `hostnetwork: true`\r\n   -  All volume and mounts except `mon-endpoint-volume`\r\n-  `direct-tools.md`: This help file does not follow recommended k8s approach for volumes. This really shouldn't be used anymore and we can remove this topic.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n<!-- Please let us know any circumstances for reproduction of your bug. -->\r\n- Launch the toolbox pod\r\n- See the mounts and privileged mode that aren't necessary\r\n\r\n",
